---
# Rename to WORKFLOW.md after copying.
# IMPORTANT: keep this entire file ASCII-only. Symphony's Solid template
# renderer corrupts UTF-8 byte 0x85 -> 0x0A, breaking Chinese characters.
# Inject Chinese issue content via linear_graphql at runtime, not via
# Liquid {{ issue.title }} substitution.

tracker:
  kind: linear
  project_slug: "<your-project-slug>"
  active_states:
    - Todo
    - "In Progress"
  terminal_states:
    - Done
    - Cancelled
    - Canceled

polling:
  interval_ms: 8000

workspace:
  root: ~/symphony-<your>-workspaces

hooks:
  after_create: |
    mkdir -p input output
  before_remove: |
    ARCHIVE_ROOT="$HOME/symphony-<your>-archive"
    mkdir -p "$ARCHIVE_ROOT/$(basename "$PWD")-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)"
    cp -r . "$ARCHIVE_ROOT/$(basename "$PWD")-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)/" 2>/dev/null || true

agent:
  max_concurrent_agents: 2
  max_turns: 15

codex:
  command: codex --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox --config shell_environment_policy.inherit=all --config 'model="gpt-5.5"' --config model_reasoning_effort=xhigh app-server
  approval_policy: never
  thread_sandbox: danger-full-access
  turn_sandbox_policy:
    type: dangerFullAccess
---

# <Pipeline Name> Agent

You are working on Linear ticket: {{ issue.identifier }}
Current state: {{ issue.state }}
URL: {{ issue.url }}

{% if attempt %}
This is continuation attempt #{{ attempt }}. First action: read the most
recent 5 comments via linear_graphql before continuing.
{% endif %}

## CRITICAL: Issue content rule

Symphony's template engine corrupts non-ASCII characters in this prompt body.
ALWAYS fetch the issue's title, description, and labels via `linear_graphql`
at the start of every turn. Do NOT rely on `{{ issue.title }}` substitution.

## Your workflow

(Define the pipeline stages here. See profiles/content-wechat/WORKFLOW.md for
a full Tier-2 editorial pipeline example.)

## Hard constraints

- NEVER write outside the workspace cwd
- On any tool error: post error in comment, KEEP state unchanged, end turn
- On continuation (attempt > 1) MUST read comments first via linear_graphql
